For brevity, we only show the genes that were statistically significant when comparing the time zero larvae to the 8h-old larvae reared in queen cells (n = 3332) in this table. There were a further 7385 statistically significant tests when considering other time points. The complete data are available in data/time_results.csv.

library(tidyverse)
library(kableExtra)

x <- read_csv("data/time_results.csv") %>%
  filter(adj.P.Val < 0.05 & Caste == "Queen" & Time == "0 vs 8") 

gene_order <- x %>% arrange(P.Value) %>% 
  pull(`Gene symbol`) %>% unique() 

x %>%
  mutate(`Gene symbol` = factor(`Gene symbol`, gene_order)) %>%
  arrange(`Gene symbol`, Time) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  kable(digits = 3) %>%
  kable_styling()
